56.7	Crazy_Horse	Crazy Horse	Crazy Horse , literally "His-Horse-Is-Crazy" or "His-Horse-Is-Spirited"; ca. 1840 â€“ September 5, 1877) was a Native American war leader of the Oglala Lakota. He took up arms against the U.S. Federal government to fight against encroachments on the territories and way of life of the Lakota people, including leading a war party at the Battle of the Little Bighorn in June 1876.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c0/Crazy_Horse_sketch.jpg/200px-Crazy_Horse_sketch.jpg
